                        Publius Valerius (who was made the first Consul with Brutus, after the Expulsion of the Kings) had the Surname of Publicola given him, for that he was a great Lover of the People, and their Interess. Of him descended this Consular Person, who was joyned with Fabius in this Embassie. 
