                        Corythus, a Town in Tuscany, built by King Corythus, descended of Tyrrhenus, the Son of Atys, King of Maeonias, and Father to Lydus; from whom the Maeonians were called Lydians, whose Colonies were planted in this part of Italy by Tyrrhenus.

